OL,3,CJapanese man receives apology after
OL,4,Cwrongly spending over 50 years on
OL,5,Cdeath row
OL,7,FA Japanese police chief has apologised
OL,8,Fin person to a man who spent 50 years
OL,9,Fon death row for a quadruple murder,
OL,10,Fbut was acquitted last month.
OL,12,FIwao Hakamada, a former boxer, was
OL,13,Facquitted by the Shizuoka District
OL,14,FCourt, which said police and
OL,15,Fprosecutors had collaborated to
OL,16,Ffabricate and plant evidence against
OL,17,Fhim, and forced him to confess with
OL,18,Fviolent closed interrogations.
