OL,3,CJapanese man receives apology after
OL,4,Cwrongly spending over 50 years on
OL,5,Cdeath row
OL,7,FHakamada was the world's longest-
OL,8,Fserving death row prisoner and only
OL,9,Fthe fifth death row inmate to be
OL,10,Facquitted in a retrial in postwar
OL,11,FJapan, where criminal trials take
OL,12,Fyears and retrials are extremely rare.
OL,14,FHis case and acquittal have triggered
OL,15,Fcalls for more transparency in the
OL,16,Finvestigation, legal change to lower
OL,17,Fhurdles for a retrial and debate over
OL,18,Fdeath penalty in Japan.
